data_table.description: Data contain medical history information of participating subjects (and family occurrence of myocardial infarcts/stroke [n=4 variables]), describing their general physical and psychological health (all > 65 years of age), results of blood work, use of medications/multivitamins, and subjects' cognitive and emotional well being. Lifestyle information is provided through variables querying for alcohol consumption, dietary, exercise and smoking habits. Data were collected at baseline of the OLD and NEW cohort studies.
